Software architecture
\layout Standard

The following describes the class hierarchy of the application.
\layout Subsection

PDGame
\layout Standard

PDGame is a game object that handles playing the game, that is, records
 decisions from competing strategies, gives the results, and keeps record
 of the history of the decisions.
\layout Subsection

PDStrategy
\layout Standard

PDStrategy is defines an IPD strategy.
\layout Standard

It is sub-classed by TitForTatPDStrategy, RandomPDStrategy, RandomRulePDStrategy
, CooperatingPDStrategy, and DefectingPDStrategy.
\layout Subsection

PrisonerGene
\layout Subsection

PrisonGAEnv
\layout Standard

PrisonGAEnv is an evolutionary environment for evolving individuals.
 It does the actual evaluation of fitnesses by competing the solutions against
 the other IPD strategies.
